WHAT I MADE IS PRECIOUS

604
00:19:40,879 --> 00:19:43,782
NEWBIE IN THE CLUB SCHEDULE
13:30 LUNCH

605
00:19:43,849 --> 00:19:44,850
A PESCATARIAN LUNCH

606
00:19:44,917 --> 00:19:48,353
You asked us to prepare
a pescatarian meal.

607
00:19:48,420 --> 00:19:49,555
Why did you want this?

608
00:19:49,621 --> 00:19:51,456
If we don't set that limit,

609
00:19:51,523 --> 00:19:55,260
people will bring
things like tteokbokki or pizza.

610
00:19:55,327 --> 00:19:59,264
Because we stay seated
for a long time while knitting,

611
00:19:59,331 --> 00:20:03,435
it doesn't feel so great
when we eat something heavy like that.

612
00:20:03,502 --> 00:20:05,404
I thought it would be good for us

613
00:20:05,470 --> 00:20:08,106
to enjoy something a little healthier.

614
00:20:08,173 --> 00:20:09,841
-You want healthy food.
-Yes.

615
00:20:10,342 --> 00:20:11,610
I was wondering.

616
00:20:11,677 --> 00:20:13,312
While you are knitting,

617
00:20:13,378 --> 00:20:16,148
what kind of words piss you off?

618
00:20:16,215 --> 00:20:18,383
Think about the things you said today.

619
00:20:18,450 --> 00:20:19,451
WHAT KNITTERS HATE

620
00:20:19,518 --> 00:20:22,554
You were the perfect example
of people that knitters hate.

621
00:20:22,621 --> 00:20:23,855
Is it for me?

622
00:20:23,922 --> 00:20:25,090
No, it's for me.

623
00:20:25,157 --> 00:20:26,491
I'll wear them when you're done.

624
00:20:26,558 --> 00:20:27,626
1. JUST GIVE IT TO ME

625
00:20:27,693 --> 00:20:30,896
It would be better to buy this
at a store when it's on sale.

626
00:20:30,963 --> 00:20:32,831
But it's not like we're doing this

627
00:20:32,898 --> 00:20:34,766
-because we don't have money.
-Right.

628
00:20:34,833 --> 00:20:36,001
Is she peeved?

629
00:20:36,068 --> 00:20:37,236
PEEVED?

630
00:20:37,302 --> 00:20:39,171
Look at how she got worked up
at what I said!

631
00:20:39,238 --> 00:20:41,573
I slightly peeved her,
and she reacted strongly.

632
00:20:41,640 --> 00:20:43,175
You peeved all of us.

633
00:20:43,242 --> 00:20:44,509
You're right.

634
00:20:44,576 --> 00:20:46,545
I peeved you all. I apologize.

635
00:20:46,612 --> 00:20:48,146
I didn't know, but now I do.

636
00:20:48,213 --> 00:20:49,881
Tell me what I shouldn't say.

637
00:20:49,948 --> 00:20:54,386
It would be nice if everyone
put themselves in our shoes.

638
00:20:54,453 --> 00:20:56,488
For example, you wouldn't go fishing

639
00:20:56,555 --> 00:20:59,057
because you don't have
the money to buy fish, right?

640
00:20:59,124 --> 00:21:00,259
It's just a hobby.

641
00:21:00,325 --> 00:21:03,462
-I wish they would accept this as a hobby.
-Right.

642
00:21:03,528 --> 00:21:06,765
But some people think we do it
because we're broke.

643
00:21:06,832 --> 00:21:08,867
They think we're darning our clothes.

644
00:21:08,934 --> 00:21:11,770
They think you're darning your clothes
because you're broke?

645
00:21:11,837 --> 00:21:14,106
It's fun to complete a garment,

646
00:21:14,172 --> 00:21:16,608
-but it's the process that we enjoy.
-Right.

647
00:21:16,675 --> 00:21:20,045
We knit because we want to
enjoy the process.

648
00:21:20,112 --> 00:21:23,215
When I first saw the clothes you made,

649
00:21:23,715 --> 00:21:26,818
I thought you could do it
because you're skilled.

650
00:21:26,885 --> 00:21:28,954
But now that I've tried it,

651
00:21:29,021 --> 00:21:32,157
I realize how difficult
it would've been to make them.

652
00:21:32,224 --> 00:21:33,258
I admire you.

653
00:21:33,325 --> 00:21:34,359
I'm wearing my life.

654
00:21:34,426 --> 00:21:36,094
-I know.
-My life is woven into this.

655
00:21:36,161 --> 00:21:38,263
So much time goes into this.

656
00:21:38,330 --> 00:21:40,299
It took me two hours to knit this.

657
00:21:40,365 --> 00:21:43,335
If anyone asks me for it,
I don't think I can give it.

658
00:21:43,402 --> 00:21:45,771
It truly is a cool hobby.

659
00:21:45,837 --> 00:21:48,774
You can do it if you want to
do something in your spare time.

660
00:21:48,840 --> 00:21:51,009
People are on the phone
while watching Netflix,

661
00:21:51,076 --> 00:21:53,478
but knitters would knit
and complete something

662
00:21:53,545 --> 00:21:56,248
while watching Netflix.

663
00:21:56,315 --> 00:21:59,484
I think it's more productive
and efficient.

664
00:21:59,951 --> 00:22:04,790
Knitting alone is definitely fun,
but knitting with others is fun too.

665
00:22:04,856 --> 00:22:06,525
If you chat for a few hours
with other knitters,

666
00:22:06,591 --> 00:22:08,960
you feel relaxed and great afterward.

